symbol.description: Unique ticker symbol identifying the trading asset
symbol.trading_meaning: The standardized code used to identify a security on exchanges (e.g., AAPL for Apple, BTCUSD for Bitcoin)

name.description: Full name of the trading asset or company
name.trading_meaning: Human-readable name of the asset for display purposes

asset_type.trading_meaning: Categorizes assets into: stocks, crypto, forex, etfs, indices, commodities, bonds
asset_type.example: Common Stock, Digital Currency, Currency Pair

exchange.description: Stock exchange or trading venue where the asset is listed
exchange.trading_meaning: Indicates market hours, liquidity, and regulatory jurisdiction

country.description: Country where the asset is domiciled or primarily traded
country.trading_meaning: Important for tax implications, currency exposure, and geopolitical risk assessment

sector.description: Economic sector classification of the asset
sector.trading_meaning: Used for sector rotation strategies and portfolio diversification. Common sectors: Technology, Healthcare, Energy, Financial Services

industry.trading_meaning: More granular classification for industry-specific analysis and peer comparison

currency.description: Currency in which the asset is priced
currency.trading_meaning: Determines currency exposure and conversion requirements for international traders

open.description: Opening price at the start of the trading period
open.trading_meaning: First traded price of the period. Gap analysis uses open vs previous close. Opening range breakout strategies use this level.
open.trading_signals: Gap up (open > prev_close) = bullish; Gap down (open < prev_close) = bearish

high.description: Highest price reached during the trading period
high.trading_meaning: Intraday resistance level. Upper shadow in candlestick patterns. Used in calculating ATR, Stochastic, and range analysis.
high.trading_signals: Rejection from highs = selling pressure; Breaking previous highs = bullish momentum

low.description: Lowest price reached during the trading period
low.trading_meaning: Intraday support level. Lower shadow in candlestick patterns. Used in calculating ATR, Stochastic, and range analysis.
low.trading_signals: Bounce from lows = buying pressure; Breaking previous lows = bearish momentum

close.description: Closing/last traded price of the period
close.trading_meaning: Most important price for technical analysis. Most indicators use close price. Settlement price for many derivatives.
close.trading_signals: Close near high = bullish; Close near low = bearish; Close near open = indecision (doji)

previous_close.description: Closing price from the previous trading period
previous_close.trading_meaning: Reference point for calculating daily change and identifying gaps. Used for after-hours movement analysis.

volume.description: Number of shares/units traded during the period
volume.trading_meaning: Measures market participation and conviction. High volume confirms price moves; Low volume suggests weak moves.
volume.trading_signals: Volume spike + price up = strong buying; Volume spike + price down = strong selling; Low volume move = likely reversal

average_volume.description: Average trading volume over a lookback period (typically 10-30 days)
average_volume.trading_meaning: Baseline for volume comparison. Current volume / average volume = relative volume ratio.
average_volume.trading_signals: Volume > 2x average = significant activity; Volume < 0.5x average = low interest

change.description: Absolute price change from previous close (close - previous_close)
change.trading_meaning: Dollar/unit change in price. Important for position sizing and P&L calculations.

percent_change.description: Percentage price change from previous close ((close - previous_close) / previous_close * 100)
percent_change.trading_meaning: Normalized change for comparing assets of different prices. Basis for screening gainers/losers.
percent_change.trading_signals: > 5% daily move = significant; > 10% = major move; > 20% = extreme volatility

hi_lo.trading_meaning: Measures intraday volatility. Wide range = volatile trading; Narrow range = consolidation.

pct_hi_lo.description: Daily range as percentage of price ((high - low) / low * 100)
pct_hi_lo.trading_meaning: Normalized volatility measure for comparing assets. Useful for day trading stock selection.

week_52_high.description: Highest price in the last 52 weeks (1 year)
week_52_high.trading_meaning: Major resistance level. Breaking 52-week high = strong bullish signal. Used for breakout strategies.
week_52_high.trading_signals: Price near 52w high = potential breakout or resistance; Breaking 52w high on volume = very bullish

week_52_low.description: Lowest price in the last 52 weeks (1 year)
week_52_low.trading_meaning: Major support level. Breaking 52-week low = strong bearish signal. Value investors look for bounces here.
week_52_low.trading_signals: Price near 52w low = potential value or falling knife; Bounce from 52w low on volume = potentially bullish

rsi.trading_meaning: Oscillator measuring speed and magnitude of price changes. Range 0-100. Most popular momentum indicator.
rsi.trading_signals: RSI < 30 = oversold (buy signal); RSI > 70 = overbought (sell signal); Divergence with price = reversal signal
rsi.formula: RSI = 100 - (100 / (1 + RS)) where RS = avg gain / avg loss over 14 periods

stoch_k.trading_meaning: Shows where close is relative to high-low range. Range 0-100. More sensitive than %D.
stoch_k.trading_signals: %K crossing above %D = bullish; %K crossing below %D = bearish

stoch_d.trading_meaning: 3-period SMA of %K. Smoother signal line. Used for crossover signals.
stoch_d.trading_signals: %K < 20 and crossing above %D = buy; %K > 80 and crossing below %D = sell

momentum.trading_meaning: Raw momentum calculation showing acceleration/deceleration of price.
momentum.trading_signals: Positive momentum = upward acceleration; Negative momentum = downward acceleration

roc.trading_meaning: Percentage-based momentum. Shows speed of price change. Used for momentum ranking.
roc.trading_signals: ROC > 0 = bullish momentum; ROC < 0 = bearish momentum; Extreme values = potential reversal

williams_r.trading_meaning: Momentum indicator similar to Stochastic but inverted. Range -100 to 0.

sma_20.trading_meaning: Short-term trend indicator. Used for short-term trading and Bollinger Bands middle line.
sma_20.trading_signals: Price > SMA20 = short-term uptrend; Price < SMA20 = short-term downtrend; SMA20 slope indicates trend strength

sma_50.trading_meaning: Medium-term trend indicator. Key level for swing traders. Often acts as dynamic support/resistance.
sma_50.trading_signals: Price crossing SMA50 = trend change; SMA50 > SMA200 = bullish market; Golden/Death cross reference

sma_200.trading_meaning: Long-term trend indicator. Institutional reference. Defines bull/bear market boundary.
sma_200.trading_signals: Price > SMA200 = bull market; Price < SMA200 = bear market; SMA50 crossing SMA200 = major signal

ema_12.trading_meaning: Fast EMA for MACD calculation. More weight on recent prices than SMA.
ema_12.trading_signals: EMA12 > EMA26 = bullish MACD; EMA12 < EMA26 = bearish MACD

ema_26.trading_meaning: Slow EMA for MACD calculation. Signal line base.
ema_26.trading_signals: Crossover with EMA12 generates MACD signals

ema_50.trading_meaning: Medium-term EMA. Alternative to SMA50 with more responsiveness to recent price.

macd.trading_meaning: Trend-following momentum indicator. Shows relationship between two EMAs.
macd.trading_signals: MACD > 0 = bullish; MACD < 0 = bearish; Crossing signal line = trade signal

macd_signal.description: MACD Signal Line (9-period EMA of MACD)
macd_signal.trading_meaning: Trigger line for MACD crossover signals.
macd_signal.trading_signals: MACD crossing above signal = buy; MACD crossing below signal = sell

macd_histogram.trading_meaning: Visual representation of MACD/Signal difference. Shows momentum acceleration.
macd_histogram.trading_signals: Histogram increasing = momentum building; Histogram decreasing = momentum fading; Histogram crossing zero = trend change

bollinger_upper.trading_meaning: Dynamic resistance level based on volatility. Price touching = potentially overbought.
bollinger_upper.trading_signals: Price at upper band = overbought/breakout; Walking the band = strong trend

bollinger_middle.trading_meaning: Center line and dynamic support/resistance. Same as SMA20.
bollinger_middle.trading_signals: Price crossing middle = trend change; Price bouncing off = support/resistance

bollinger_lower.trading_meaning: Dynamic support level based on volatility. Price touching = potentially oversold.
bollinger_lower.trading_signals: Price at lower band = oversold/breakdown; Band squeeze = low volatility, breakout coming

atr.trading_meaning: Volatility indicator showing average price range. Used for stop-loss placement and position sizing.
atr.trading_signals: High ATR = high volatility, use wider stops; Low ATR = low volatility, potential breakout setup
atr.formula: ATR = EMA of TR; TR = max(high-low, |high-prev_close|, |low-prev_close|)

adx.trading_meaning: Measures trend strength (not direction). Range 0-100. Core trend strength indicator.
adx.trading_signals: ADX > 25 = strong trend; ADX < 20 = weak/no trend; ADX rising = trend strengthening

plus_di.trading_meaning: Measures bullish trend strength. Part of ADX system.

minus_di.trading_meaning: Measures bearish trend strength. Part of ADX system.

cci.trading_meaning: Oscillator measuring price relative to average. Range typically -300 to +300.
cci.trading_signals: CCI > 100 = overbought; CCI < -100 = oversold; CCI crossing 0 = trend change

ultimate_osc.trading_meaning: Combines short, medium, and long-term momentum. Range 0-100.
ultimate_osc.trading_signals: UO > 70 = overbought; UO < 30 = oversold; Divergence = reversal signal

awesome_osc.trading_meaning: Momentum indicator comparing recent momentum to larger momentum. Histogram format.
awesome_osc.trading_signals: AO > 0 = bullish momentum; AO < 0 = bearish momentum; Twin peaks = reversal signal
awesome_osc.formula: AO = SMA(5, Median Price) - SMA(34, Median Price)

obv.trading_meaning: Cumulative volume indicator. Shows if volume is flowing into or out of the asset.
obv.trading_signals: OBV rising with price = confirmed uptrend; OBV falling with price rising = potential reversal
obv.formula: OBV adds volume on up days, subtracts on down days

pvo.trading_meaning: Shows relationship between two volume EMAs. Similar to MACD for volume.
pvo.trading_signals: PVO > 0 = above average volume activity; PVO crossing signal line = volume momentum change

ppo.trading_meaning: MACD expressed as percentage. Useful for comparing different priced assets.
ppo.trading_signals: Similar to MACD but normalized; PPO > 0 = bullish; PPO < 0 = bearish

kama.trading_meaning: Adaptive moving average that adjusts to market volatility. Less whipsaws than traditional MAs.
kama.trading_signals: Price > KAMA = uptrend; Price < KAMA = downtrend; KAMA slope shows trend direction

trix.trading_meaning: Triple smoothed exponential moving average. Filters out market noise.
trix.trading_signals: TRIX > 0 = bullish; TRIX < 0 = bearish; TRIX crossing zero = potential trend change

datetime.trading_meaning: When the candle/bar closed. Essential for time-series analysis and backtesting.

timestamp.trading_meaning: Machine-readable time format. Useful for calculations and sorting.

created_at.description: When the record was inserted into the database
created_at.trading_meaning: Data freshness indicator. Useful for debugging and audit trails.

data_source.trading_meaning: Identifies API source (TwelveData, Kraken, etc.). Important for data quality assessment.

stocks.description: Equities - ownership shares in public companies
stocks.trading_hours: US markets: 9:30 AM - 4:00 PM ET (pre/post market available)

indices.description: Market Indices - benchmarks representing market segments

5min.strategies: Scalping, momentum plays, opening range breakouts

hourly.use_case: Day trading and short-term swing trading
hourly.strategies: Intraday trends, session trading, short swings

weekly_summary.strategies: Long-term trends, sector rotation, value investing

historical_daily.strategies: Strategy backtesting, statistical analysis, machine learning training
